<subSubSection lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,706,1621,1647]" box="[151,706,1621,1647]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,706,1621,1647]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Key to species and subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[559,706,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Yungasacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[559,706,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Yungasacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<key lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1690,2035]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
1. Male tegmina broad in proximal half, with long stridulatory vein and rather wide mirror; male cerci long, with short basal part (proximal to base of inner branch), with short widened part (distal of base of inner branch), and with very long remaining part (this part narrow and longer than previous parts together...................................................... 
<specimenCount pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="male">2 Male</specimenCount>
tegmina clearly narrower in proximal half, with distinctly shorter stridulatory vein and narrower mirror; male cerci diverse in length, with clearly longer basal or middle (widened) parts, and narrow remaining part shorter................. 3
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1690,2035]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyStep pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
2. Pronotal disc with a pair of dark oblique posterior stripes reaching to middle; male cerci in lateral view with widened sub-basal part longer than the more distal part (
<figureCitation box="[575,662,1866,1888]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@41.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 23. Yungasacris species. A, G–H. Y. multa. Male habitus, cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. B–C. Y. grata grata cerci in dorsal and lateral view. D. Y. grata rara cerci in lateral view. E–F. Y. peruviana cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. (Figs. B–F. after Rehn, 1950, Figs. D, G–H. after Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gorochov, 2013)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876271/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
); male subgenital plate with short but well-developed styli and shallow emargination between them................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1950 Pronotal" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[1185,1436,1895,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Yungasacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="grata" subSpecies="grata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1185,1320,1896,1917]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Y. grata grata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn, J. A. G." box="[1326,1436,1895,1917]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="271 - 319" refId="ref42693" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1950 [1949]) Studies in the Group Dysoniae (Aphidniae of authors) (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) Part I. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 75 (3 - 4), 271 - 319." type="journal article" year="1950">Rehn, 1950</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
Pronotal disc with a pair of dark oblique posterior stripes not reaching middle; male cerci in lateral view with widened subbasal part not longer than more distal part (
<figureCitation box="[596,687,1954,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@41.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 23. Yungasacris species. A, G–H. Y. multa. Male habitus, cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. B–C. Y. grata grata cerci in dorsal and lateral view. D. Y. grata rara cerci in lateral view. E–F. Y. peruviana cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. (Figs. B–F. after Rehn, 1950, Figs. D, G–H. after Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gorochov, 2013)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876271/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 23D</figureCitation>
); male subgenital plate without distinct styli and with rather deep emargination......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorochov, 2013" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2013" box="[1150,1436,1983,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Yungasacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="grata" subSpecies="rara">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1150,1276,1984,2005]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Y. grata rara</emphasis>
Gorochov, 2013
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1690,2035]" lastBlockId="40.[226,1437,151,291]" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,2013,2035]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<keyStep box="[151,1436,2013,2035]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">3. Pronotum without distinct traces of dark markings; male cerci with basal part (proximal to base of inner branch) shorter than</keyStep>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<keyStep pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
widened middle part, with narrow distal part almost equal to middle part in length, and in lateral view with dorsal subbasal convexity (
<figureCitation box="[334,455,181,203]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@41.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 23. Yungasacris species. A, G–H. Y. multa. Male habitus, cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. B–C. Y. grata grata cerci in dorsal and lateral view. D. Y. grata rara cerci in lateral view. E–F. Y. peruviana cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. (Figs. B–F. after Rehn, 1950, Figs. D, G–H. after Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gorochov, 2013)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876271/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs. 23E, F</figureCitation>
)............................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1950 Pronotum" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Yungasacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1195,1320,181,202]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Y. peruviana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn, J. A. G." box="[1326,1436,181,203]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="271 - 319" refId="ref42693" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1950 [1949]) Studies in the Group Dysoniae (Aphidniae of authors) (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) Part I. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 75 (3 - 4), 271 - 319." type="journal article" year="1950">Rehn, 1950</bibRefCitation>
Pronotum
</taxonomicName>
with distinct dark marks; male cerci with basal part (proximal to base of inner branch) longer than widened middle part, with narrow distal part distinctly longer than middle part (
<figureCitation box="[838,928,239,261]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@41.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 23. Yungasacris species. A, G–H. Y. multa. Male habitus, cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. B–C. Y. grata grata cerci in dorsal and lateral view. D. Y. grata rara cerci in lateral view. E–F. Y. peruviana cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. (Figs. B–F. after Rehn, 1950, Figs. D, G–H. after Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gorochov, 2013)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876271/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 23G</figureCitation>
), and in profile without any dorsal convexity in subbasal part (
<figureCitation box="[332,421,269,291]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@41.[153,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 23. Yungasacris species. A, G–H. Y. multa. Male habitus, cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. B–C. Y. grata grata cerci in dorsal and lateral view. D. Y. grata rara cerci in lateral view. E–F. Y. peruviana cerci in dorsal and lateral view respectively. (Figs. B–F. after Rehn, 1950, Figs. D, G–H. after Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gorochov, 2013)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876271" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876271/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 23H</figureCitation>
).............................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castaneda &amp; Gorochov, 2013" authorityName="Cadena-Castaneda &amp; Gorochov" authorityYear="2013" box="[984,1436,268,291]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Yungasacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1066,268,290]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Y. multa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Gorochov, A. V." box="[1073,1436,269,291]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="189 - 203" refId="ref39416" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Gorochov, A. V. (2013) Review of the Neotropical genera Quiva and Yungasacris (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 22 (2), 189 - 203." type="journal article" year="2013">Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gorochov, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
